  <h2 id="overview" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-u-padding__bottom--600 vf-search-client-side--no-index">Overview</h2>
  <p>Governance and compliance make LRO enforceable at organisational level so that performance, accessibility, resilience, and efficiency are sustained over time instead of treated as one-off initiatives.</p>

  <p><strong>Key idea:</strong> make performance and accessibility enforceable, not advisory. Governance defines standards and ownership; compliance validates adherence through measurable checks.</p>

  <h2 id="why-lro" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Why this matters for LRO</h2>
  <h3>User impact</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Consistent experience across services and teams</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Reduced long-term performance regression</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Better accessibility and inclusivity</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Lower data and cost burden for users</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Risks if ignored</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Performance degrades over time</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Inconsistent implementation across products</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Accessibility and usability gaps persist</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Regulatory and legal risk increases</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="common-problems" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Common problems</h2>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">No formal LRO standards or performance policies</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">No clear accountability for optimisation outcomes</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">One-time audits without follow-up</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Ownership of performance metrics is unclear</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Compliance focus limited to accessibility only</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="design-principles" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Design principles involved</h2>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Continuous compliance, not point-in-time checks</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Clear ownership and accountability</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Standardisation across teams and products</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Transparent metrics and reporting</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Inclusivity, accessibility, and sustainability</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Risk-based prioritisation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="strategy-options" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Strategy options</h2>

  <h3>LRO compliance checklist</h3>
  <p>Use a structured checklist across performance, accessibility, efficiency, resilience, compatibility, and security.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Performance:</strong> page size budgets, Core Web Vitals, loading strategy</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Accessibility:</strong> WCAG checks, keyboard support, semantic structure</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Efficiency:</strong> compression, image optimisation, caching, third-party limits</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Resilience:</strong> retries, offline fallback, graceful degradation</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Compatibility:</strong> low-end devices, constrained CPU and memory</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Security/privacy:</strong> secure handling and minimal data collection</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Periodic audit cycle</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Baseline assessment and gap analysis</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Remediation planning and tracking</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Re-evaluation with field data</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Quarterly for major systems, more frequent for critical platforms</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Governance model</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Product owners accountable for compliance outcomes</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Engineering teams accountable for implementation quality</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">QA validates performance, accessibility, and usability</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Leadership ensures prioritisation, funding, and enforcement</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Policy and standards definition</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Define enforceable performance budgets and accessibility thresholds</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Set data usage and device compatibility expectations</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Align to recognised standards and local constraints</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="implementation" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Implementation guidance</h2>
  <ol class="vf-list vf-list--ordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Define LRO governance policies and measurable standards</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Establish compliance checklists and release gates</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Create recurring audit cycles and ownership model</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Integrate real-user monitoring and regression alerts</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Prioritise high-risk areas and continuously refine controls</li>
  </ol>

